---
import PortalLayout from '../layouts/PortalLayout.astro'
---

<PortalLayout
  title="Publishing — Sohma Institute"
  description="Four open-access publishing streams: a peer-reviewed journal, clinical protocol monographs, working papers, and a division-specific textbook series."
>
  <article class="pub-page">

    <!-- HERO -->
    <header class="pub-hero">
      <div class="hero-inner">
        <div class="section-label">Publishing</div>
        <h1 class="hero-title">Knowledge Dissemination</h1>
        <p class="hero-lead">The Institute controls its own dissemination pipeline. Four publishing streams — all open access or practitioner-accessible — feed directly back into the clinical and education ecosystem.</p>
      </div>
    </header>


    <!-- ═══════════ JOURNAL ═══════════ -->
    <section class="pub-section" id="journal">
      <div class="pub-section-top">
        <span class="pub-section-num">01</span>
        <div class="pub-heading-row">
          <h2 class="pub-section-heading">Journal of Traditional & Network Medicine</h2>
          <span class="pub-status pre-launch">Pre-Launch</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="pub-section-tagline">Peer-reviewed, open-access. Original research, systematic reviews, case series.</p>

      <div class="pub-two-col">
        <div>
          <h3>Editorial Position</h3>
          <p>The journal is committed to whole-systems research design. Most journals in this space default to reductionist methodology — isolating single compounds, forcing complex interventions into RCT designs built for molecular entities. This journal publishes research that preserves intervention complexity. N-of-1 adaptive trials, practice-based evidence networks, network pharmacology, and mixed-methods designs that capture what mono-variable designs systematically destroy.</p>

          <h3>Open Access Policy</h3>
          <p>All published research is freely available under Creative Commons licensing. No article processing charges at launch. The Institute's position is that traditional medicine knowledge was never proprietary and its validation shouldn't be either.</p>

          <h3>For Authors</h3>
          <p>Submission guidelines, editorial board composition, and the double-blind review process will be published when the journal opens for submissions. Target launch date will be announced following establishment of the inaugural editorial board.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Indexing Roadmap</h3>
          <div class="pub-roadmap">
            <div class="pub-roadmap-item">
              <div class="pub-roadmap-marker"></div>
              <div class="pub-roadmap-content">
                <span class="pub-roadmap-label">DOAJ Registration</span>
                <span class="pub-roadmap-timeline">Year 1</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="pub-roadmap-item">
              <div class="pub-roadmap-marker"></div>
              <div class="pub-roadmap-content">
                <span class="pub-roadmap-label">Scopus Indexing</span>
                <span class="pub-roadmap-timeline">Within 3 years</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="pub-roadmap-item">
              <div class="pub-roadmap-marker"></div>
              <div class="pub-roadmap-content">
                <span class="pub-roadmap-label">PubMed Central</span>
                <span class="pub-roadmap-timeline">Following Scopus</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="pub-note">Transparent about indexing status. An un-indexed journal with a clear roadmap is more credible than one that obscures where it stands.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- ═══════════ MONOGRAPHS ═══════════ -->
    <section class="pub-section" id="monographs">
      <div class="pub-section-top">
        <span class="pub-section-num">02</span>
        <div class="pub-heading-row">
          <h2 class="pub-section-heading">Protocol Monograph Series</h2>
          <span class="pub-status in-dev">In Development</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="pub-section-tagline">Detailed clinical protocol documents for network practitioners. Living references that evolve with registry data.</p>

      <div class="pub-two-col">
        <div>
          <h3>What They Are</h3>
          <p>Each monograph covers a specific clinical protocol in full: evidence summary, prescribing guidelines, outcome measures, contraindications, drug interaction tables, and patient communication frameworks. These are not textbooks — they are living reference documents that evolve as outcome data accumulates from the practitioner network registry.</p>

          <h3>Update Cycle</h3>
          <p>Monographs are version-controlled with published change logs. When new clinical outcome data comes in from the network registry, relevant monographs are updated on a defined review cycle. Practitioners know exactly what changed and why — no silent revisions.</p>

          <h3>Access</h3>
          <p>Monograph content is available through the practitioner portal for credentialed network members. If you're already a member, <a href="#">log in to access the library</a>. If you're not yet part of the network, <a href="/network">learn about membership</a>.</p>
          <p>One monograph (or a redacted excerpt) will be made publicly available as a demonstration of the series' quality and clinical rigour.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Monograph Structure</h3>
          <div class="pub-roadmap">
            <div class="pub-roadmap-item">
              <div class="pub-roadmap-marker"></div>
              <div class="pub-roadmap-content">
                <span class="pub-roadmap-label">Evidence Summary</span>
                <span class="pub-roadmap-timeline">Systematic review of current literature</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="pub-roadmap-item">
              <div class="pub-roadmap-marker"></div>
              <div class="pub-roadmap-content">
                <span class="pub-roadmap-label">Prescribing Protocol</span>
                <span class="pub-roadmap-timeline">Dosing, titration, product selection</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="pub-roadmap-item">
              <div class="pub-roadmap-marker"></div>
              <div class="pub-roadmap-content">
                <span class="pub-roadmap-label">Outcome Measures</span>
                <span class="pub-roadmap-timeline">Standardised assessment tools</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="pub-roadmap-item">
              <div class="pub-roadmap-marker"></div>
              <div class="pub-roadmap-content">
                <span class="pub-roadmap-label">Contraindications</span>
                <span class="pub-roadmap-timeline">Safety screening, drug interactions</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="pub-roadmap-item">
              <div class="pub-roadmap-marker"></div>
              <div class="pub-roadmap-content">
                <span class="pub-roadmap-label">Change Log</span>
                <span class="pub-roadmap-timeline">Version history with rationale</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- ═══════════ WORKING PAPERS ═══════════ -->
    <section class="pub-section" id="working-papers">
      <div class="pub-section-top">
        <span class="pub-section-num">03</span>
        <div class="pub-heading-row">
          <h2 class="pub-section-heading">Institute Working Papers</h2>
          <span class="pub-status open">Open Access</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="pub-section-tagline">Pre-publication working papers. Emerging research, policy analysis, and theoretical contributions — the Institute's rapid-response channel.</p>

      <div class="pub-two-col">
        <div>
          <h3>What They Are</h3>
          <p>When the TGA changes cannabis prescribing rules, when NHMRC updates research guidelines, when new evidence challenges established clinical frameworks — the working paper series is how the Institute responds publicly. These are time-sensitive, pre-publication documents: preliminary findings, regulatory commentary, theoretical position papers.</p>
          <p>Working papers are distinct from the whitepapers on this site. Whitepapers are canonical position documents. Working papers are time-sensitive, may be superseded, and represent the Institute's evolving thinking rather than its settled positions.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Access & Format</h3>
          <p>Fully open. Each working paper is published with title, abstract, date, author(s), division tag(s), and PDF download. Filterable by division and topic.</p>

          <h3>Publication Cycle</h3>
          <p>Rapid. Working papers are reviewed by at least two Institute faculty members but are not subject to external peer review. They are explicitly marked as pre-publication and may be revised, superseded, or withdrawn as the evidence base evolves.</p>

          <div class="pub-archive-status">
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/></svg>
            <span>Archive launching with first publication — check back soon.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- ═══════════ TEXTBOOKS ═══════════ -->
    <section class="pub-section" id="textbooks">
      <div class="pub-section-top">
        <span class="pub-section-num">04</span>
        <div class="pub-heading-row">
          <h2 class="pub-section-heading">Textbook Series</h2>
          <span class="pub-status in-dev">In Development</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="pub-section-tagline">Division-specific textbooks authored by Institute faculty. Written for the convergence thesis framework and case-based pedagogy — not generic natural medicine texts repackaged.</p>

      <div class="pub-two-col">
        <div>
          <h3>What They Are</h3>
          <p>Each textbook is authored specifically for the Institute's pedagogical framework: case-based architecture, inverse classroom delivery, and portfolio assessment. They integrate the convergence thesis throughout — not as an add-on chapter, but as the organising principle for how clinical knowledge is structured and applied.</p>
          <p>These are required texts for enrolled students and will be available for independent purchase by practitioners and institutions.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Development Pipeline</h3>
          <div class="pub-pipeline">
            <div class="pub-pipeline-item">
              <span class="pub-pipeline-division">Division I</span>
              <span class="pub-pipeline-title">Complex Herbal Medicines</span>
              <span class="pub-pipeline-status writing">In Writing</span>
            </div>
            <div class="pub-pipeline-item">
              <span class="pub-pipeline-division">Division II</span>
              <span class="pub-pipeline-title">Emergent & Entheogenic Modalities</span>
              <span class="pub-pipeline-status writing">In Writing</span>
            </div>
            <div class="pub-pipeline-item">
              <span class="pub-pipeline-division">Division III</span>
              <span class="pub-pipeline-title">East-Asian Medicine & Acupuncture</span>
              <span class="pub-pipeline-status planned">Planned</span>
            </div>
            <div class="pub-pipeline-item">
              <span class="pub-pipeline-division">Division IV</span>
              <span class="pub-pipeline-title">Nutritional & Environmental Medicine</span>
              <span class="pub-pipeline-status planned">Planned</span>
            </div>
            <div class="pub-pipeline-item">
              <span class="pub-pipeline-division">Division V</span>
              <span class="pub-pipeline-title">Lifestyle & Relational Medicine</span>
              <span class="pub-pipeline-status planned">Planned</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="pub-note">Transparent about the pipeline. Two titles in active writing; three planned following division establishment. No purchase links until manuscripts are complete.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="pub-cta">
      <div class="pub-cta-inner">
        <h2>Contribute</h2>
        <p>The Institute welcomes research submissions, working paper proposals, and expressions of interest for editorial board positions. If your work aligns with whole-systems research design and the convergence thesis, we want to hear from you.</p>
        <div class="pub-cta-buttons">
          <a href="/contact" class="cta-primary">Publishing Enquiry</a>
          <a href="/research" class="cta-secondary">View Research Programs</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</PortalLayout>

<style>
  .pub-page {
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    padding: 0 clamp(20px, 3vw, 40px);
  }
  .pub-page p { line-height: 1.8; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
  .pub-page p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .pub-page h2, .pub-page h3 { margin: 0; }
  .pub-page a { color: var(--accent-dark); }

  .section-label {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    color: var(--accent-dark);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .section-label::after {
    content: '';
    flex: 1;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--accent-line);
  }


  /* ═══════════ HERO ═══════════ */
  .pub-hero {
    position: relative;
    max-width: none;
    margin: 0 calc(-40px - clamp(20px, 3vw, 40px));
    padding: 0;
    background: var(--bg-hero);
  }

  .hero-inner {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 96px calc(2rem + 40px + clamp(20px, 3vw, 40px)) 64px calc(1rem + 40px + clamp(20px, 3vw, 40px));
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4.25rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 0 24px;
  }

  .hero-lead {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 640px;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .pub-nav {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .pub-page .pub-nav a {
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 6px 14px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, color 0.2s;
  }

  .pub-page .pub-nav a:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent-border-30);
    color: var(--accent-dark);
  }


  /* ═══════════ SECTIONS ═══════════ */
  .pub-section {
    padding: 2.5rem calc(40px + clamp(20px, 3vw, 40px));
    border-radius: 0;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    margin-left: calc(-40px - clamp(20px, 3vw, 40px));
    margin-right: calc(-40px - clamp(20px, 3vw, 40px));
  }

  .pub-section:last-of-type {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  #journal { background: rgba(245, 243, 239, 1); }
  #monographs { background: rgba(240, 242, 240, 1); }
  #working-papers { background: rgba(243, 243, 246, 1); }
  #textbooks { background: rgba(244, 241, 237, 1); }

  .pub-section-top {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .pub-heading-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .pub-section-num {
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .pub-section-heading {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 2.1rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    scroll-margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .pub-status {
    font-size: 0.625rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #fff;
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 3px 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    align-self: flex-start;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .pub-status.pre-launch { background: var(--chart-warm); }
  .pub-status.in-dev { background: var(--chart-blue); }
  .pub-status.open { background: var(--accent-green); }

  .pub-page p.pub-section-tagline {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-body-65);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 0 3rem;
  }


  /* ═══════════ TWO COL ═══════════ */
  .pub-two-col {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
  }

  .pub-two-col h3 {
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .pub-two-col h3:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .pub-two-col p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-body-70);
  }

  .pub-note {
    font-size: 0.8125rem !important;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-tertiary) !important;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }


  /* ═══════════ ROADMAP ═══════════ */
  .pub-roadmap {
    position: relative;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-left: 24px;
  }

  .pub-roadmap-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    padding: 1.75rem 0;
    position: relative;
  }

  .pub-roadmap-item:first-child { padding-top: 0; }
  .pub-roadmap-item:last-child { padding-bottom: 0; }

  .pub-roadmap-item:not(:last-child)::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: -18px;
    top: 14px;
    bottom: -1.75rem;
    width: 1px;
    background: var(--border-light);
    z-index: 0;
  }

  .pub-roadmap-item:first-child:not(:last-child)::before {
    top: 9px;
  }

  .pub-roadmap-marker {
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: none;
    background: var(--text-heading);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 4px;
    margin-left: -22px;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .pub-roadmap-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.125rem;
  }

  .pub-roadmap-label {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-heading);
  }

  .pub-roadmap-timeline {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }




  /* ═══════════ ARCHIVE STATUS ═══════════ */
  .pub-archive-status {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .pub-archive-status svg {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    opacity: 0.5;
  }


  /* ═══════════ PIPELINE ═══════════ */
  .pub-pipeline {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .pub-pipeline-item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr auto;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.625rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  }

  .pub-pipeline-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .pub-pipeline-division {
    font-size: 0.625rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .pub-pipeline-title {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .pub-pipeline-status {
    font-size: 0.5625rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: #fff;
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 2px 8px;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .pub-pipeline-status.writing { background: var(--accent-green); }
  .pub-pipeline-status.planned { background: var(--text-tertiary); }


  /* ═══════════ CTA ═══════════ */
  .pub-cta {
    padding: 3rem 0 4rem;
  }

  .pub-cta-inner {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 540px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .pub-cta-inner h2 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 2.75rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .pub-cta-inner p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-body-60);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .pub-cta-buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .pub-page .cta-primary {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: #fff;
    background: var(--accent-dark);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 12px 28px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }
  .pub-page .cta-primary:hover { background: var(--accent-darker-hover); color: #fff; }

  .pub-page .cta-secondary {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--glass-12);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 12px 28px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, color 0.2s;
  }
  .pub-page .cta-secondary:hover { border-color: var(--accent-border-30); color: var(--accent-dark); }


  /* ═══════════ RESPONSIVE ═══════════ */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .pub-hero { margin: 0 -20px; }
    .hero-inner { padding: 48px 1.25rem 36px; }
    .hero-title { font-size: 2.5rem; }
    .hero-lead { padding-left: 0; }
    .pub-nav { padding-left: 0; }
    .pub-two-col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; }
    .pub-section-heading { font-size: 1.75rem; }
    .pub-pipeline-item { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.25rem; }
  }
</style>
